Package au.csiro.pathling.fhirpath

Interface Temporal

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DateLiteralPath, DatePath, DateTimeLiteralPath, DateTimePath
    public interface Temporal
    Describes a path that represents a temporal value such as DateTime or Date, and can be the subject of date arithmetic operations involving time durations.
    Author:
    John Grimes

        Gets a function that can take the QuantityLiteralPath representing a time duration and return a FhirPath that contains the result of date arithmetic operation for this path and the provided duration. The type of operation is controlled by supplying a Numeric.MathOperation.
        Parameters:
        operation - The Numeric.MathOperation type to retrieve a result for
        dataset - The Dataset to use within the result
        expression - The FHIRPath expression to use within the result
        Returns:
        A Function that takes a QuantityLiteralPath as its parameter, and returns a FhirPath.

      • buildDateArithmeticOperation

        @Nonnull
static Function<QuantityLiteralPath,​FhirPath> buildDateArithmeticOperation​(@Nonnull
                                                                                 FhirPath source,
                                                                                 @Nonnull
                                                                                 Numeric.MathOperation operation,
                                                                                 @Nonnull
                                                                                 Dataset<Row> dataset,
                                                                                 @Nonnull
                                                                                 String expression,
                                                                                 String additionFunctionName,
                                                                                 String subtractionFunctionName)
        Gets a function that can take the QuantityLiteralPath representing a time duration and return a FhirPath that contains the result of applying the date arithmetic operation for to the source path and the provided duration. The type of operation is controlled by supplying a Numeric.MathOperation.
        Parameters:
        source - the FhirPath to which the operation should be applied to. Should be a Temporal path.
        operation - The Numeric.MathOperation type to retrieve a result for
        dataset - The Dataset to use within the result
        expression - the FHIRPath expression to use within the result
        additionFunctionName - the name of the UDF to use for additions.
        subtractionFunctionName - the name of the UDF to use for subtractions.
        Returns:
        A Function that takes a QuantityLiteralPath as its parameter, and returns a FhirPath.
